# English Teacher Chatbot

Next.js 16 App Router app: AI English practice chat with token-gated access.

## Stack

- **Next.js** 16.2.x, **React** 19, **TypeScript** (strict)
- **Tailwind CSS** v4 (`@import "tailwindcss"` in `app/globals.css`)
- **shadcn/ui** (base-nova, `@base-ui/react`) — add components via `components.json`
- **Vercel AI SDK** (`ai`, `@ai-sdk/react`, `@ai-sdk/openai`) + **OpenRouter**
- Path alias: `@/*` → project root

## Layout

| Area | Role |
|------|------|
| `app/page.tsx` | Client chat UI (`useChat`) |
| `app/login/page.tsx` | Token login (`useActionState` + server action) |
| `app/api/chat/route.ts` | Streaming chat API (edge runtime) |
| `app/actions/auth.ts` | `loginAction`, `logoutAction` |
| `proxy.ts` | Auth gate (replaces deprecated `middleware`) |
| `lib/auth.ts` | HMAC session cookie |
| `lib/rate-limit.ts` | In-memory login rate limit (per IP) |
| `components/NavBar.tsx` | External links + logout |
| `components/ui/*` | shadcn primitives |

## Environment (`.env.local`)

- `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` — OpenRouter API key
- `OPENROUTER_MODEL` — e.g. `openai/gpt-oss-120b:free` (fallback in code if unset)
- `LOGIN_TOKEN` — shared access token for login (required for auth)

Never commit `.env.local` or secrets. Do not log env values.

## Commands

- `npm run dev` — dev server
- `npm run build` / `npm run start` — production
- `npm run lint` — ESLint (eslint-config-next)

## Scope when editing

- Prefer minimal diffs; match existing file style (quotes, semicolons vary by file).
- Extend `NAV_LINKS` in `NavBar.tsx` for new top nav items (external `target="_blank"`).
- Chat max width and nav use `max-w-2xl` — keep new pages visually consistent.
